# 11. 论文里应该怎么写差异

建议 intro 里加一段非常明确的话：

> Concurrent work has shown that GUI grounding errors are largely determined before decoding and proposes to revisit the prefill stage with attention-guided re-prefill. Our work asks a different question: within the prefill computation itself, where is the spatial target represented? We find that GUI grounding is not uniformly encoded across prefill layers. Instead, spatial posteriors peak in middle layers and can deteriorate in final layers, while late layers become better aligned with coordinate/action serialization. This layerwise spatial-to-serialization transition motivates decoding grounding from intermediate representations rather than treating prefill attention as a single aggregated signal.

这段能把边界讲清楚。

